name: Chris Satterfield
findings:
- Partial avulsion of soft tissues in lower extremities
- Penetrating injuries with irregular wound margins
- Vertebral fractures at T5
- Evidence consistent with predatory animal attack
conclusion: Cause of death due to exsanguination from animal-inflicted trauma.

name: James Anderson
findings:
- Multiple incised wounds across the neck region
- Jugular vein and trachea severed
- Surrounding bruising consistent with forceful assault
- No evidence suggesting self-inflicted injury
conclusion: Cause of death determined as homicidal sharp-force trauma, with fatal injuries caused by repeated stabbing with a knife.

name: Molly Sanford

name: Cletus Blick

name: Michael Thompson
findings:

name: Ivan Lofer
findings:
- Two gunshot wounds identified: one in the thorax, one in the upper limb
- Thoracic wound penetrated lung tissue causing hemothorax (~1180 mL blood)
- Upper limb wound traversed soft tissue, non-fatal
- Trajectory indicates assailant at lower angle relative to victim
conclusion: Cause of death determined as firearm-related ballistic trauma, with fatal injuries resulting in massive hemorrhage and organ perforation. Manner of death: homicide.

name: Mark Sullivan

- Projectile lodged near T3 vertebra
conclusion: Cause of death determined as firearm-related ballistic trauma, with fatal injuries resulting in massive hemorrhage and organ perforation. Manner of death: homicide.
